Author: Alright#0419
Content: for example let's say a fungible chain is created with 1 LABS per block. After 1000 blocks, the emission of this chain is 1000 LABS. If 10000 LABS are transferred to this chain, the most that can be exported back to mainchain is 10000. This means that exporting 1000 of this chain back to the main chain would result in ~909 coins coming back to the main chain

Author: Alright#0419
Content: so (total coins transferred / total coins on chain) would be the fungibility rate
